SUMMARY:The Pence Joins Yolo Fest This Spring!
DESCRIPTION:The Pence Joins Yolo Fest This Spring! \nThe Pence Gallery\, a unique nonprofit art gallery highlighting local & regional artists\, is participating in the county-wide Yolo Fest this spring. From March 27-29\, 2026\, Yolo Fest celebrates the region’s agriculture\, music\, arts\, culture\, farm-to-table food\, craft beverages\, recreation\, and local hospitality. \nThe Pence Gallery in Davis will be open with three spectacular art exhibits from 11:30 AM – 5 PM\, and admission is free to view these displays by these visual artists: \nManuel Fernando Rios: When They Reminisce Over You\nFebruary 7 – March 29\nIn his exhibit\, Rios shares his interest in themes that explore his Chicano heritage\, as well as his family’s history and experiences. Blurring the line between naturalism and abstraction\, the artist embraces the use of complex design patterns\, photography\, and text to make a powerful statement. \nAssorted Flavors: Pence Member Exhibit\nMarch 13 – April 16\nView 40 works of art created by Pence Members in this widely ranging annual display of paintings\, photographs\, textiles\, and more. \nBarbara Prodaniuk: Myths in Mud\nMarch 13 – April 26\nProdaniuk is a ceramic artist whose work is inspired by the forest\, meadows\, and waterways of the Truckee area. She explores stories carried by the animals and artifacts found in these environments. \nSpecial Weekend Activities \nSelf-guided Scavenger Hunt:\nMarch 28-29\, 11:30 AM – 4:30 PM\nFree to participate!\nJoin us for a fun\, art-themed scavenger hunt at the gallery by exploring the Pence’s exhibits. Complete all of the clues for the chance to be entered in a raffle to win a $25 gift certificate to the Pence gift store! A raffle winner will be selected and contacted at 4:30 PM on both Saturday and Sunday. \nPrintmaking for All Ages\nSunday\, March 29\, 1-3 PM\n$5 Members | $10 Non-Members (per person\, all materials included)\nIn this workshop\, printmaking is made easy! Learn how to create bold and colorful block prints using a Styrofoam plate\, printmaking ink\, and a few simple tricks and techniques. This is a drop-in program for all ages\, and no sign-ups are required in advance. Children ages 5 and up may participate if they are accompanied by an adult.
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/the-pence-joins-yolo-fest-this-spring/
LOCATION:Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA\, 95616\, United States
CATEGORIES:Art,Bring the Kids,Community
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Yolo-Fest-Banner.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Pence Gallery":MAILTO:pencegallery@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
